\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Why a User becomes inactive
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Logit
\series default
: Biulding model here is easy, logistic regression would work here.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Interpreation
\series default
: becasue the purpose of model is
\series bold
 not only prediction, but also interpreation
\series default
.
 Because we want to understand which variable causes the inactivity.
 So you really want to use some glassbox model rather than black box.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Probability
\series default
: Also when you want to classify 0,1, you want something can give you a
 probability, rather than just give you 0 or 1
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Then you can use these probability to design some action
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Action Plan
\series default
: For example, if we forsee a high value customer will become inactive,
 then you want to call him, or give him better offers.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Feature
\series default
: Finding out the exact correct features is the key.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
