\begin_layout Subsection
Pagerank to measure importance/influence of user
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The idea is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The importance of a user depends on number of followers, and also depend
 on the importance of those followers.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If an influential celebrity A follows B, then B must also has certain importance.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Pagerank algorithm is using this idea to measure how importance/influence
 of a point in the network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The way it works is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Image you want to do a random work through all the social network, starting
 from point A, as A is following N people the probability that A travels
 to each followees 1/N.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Then assume now we travel from A to B, then do a random walk to the people
 that B follows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
You keep doing one millions of time, and it turned out the probability/number
 of times of getting to a certain point will converge to a steady value.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
That value is the score of the importance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
the idea is: if the more people follow a point A, then it is easier to get
 their.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection
Path Find to measure importance of a user
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
You can think about this problem as a path finding problem: How to find
 the shortest parth to travel from one user to another user.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If you randomly select two points in the scoial network, both A and B have
 no common firends in the real world, but they both follow one musician
 in Twitter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
You do this test millions times --- each time you randomly select two points
 and calculating the clost path.
 The more common trespassing / transiting points are those celebrities.
\end_layout

