\begin_layout Section
Twitter Products
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All of this falls under the line of two of the most important use cases
 that we want to focus on, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
News.
 And we think Twitter is better at real-time news and live news than anyone
 else on the platform – in the world, I should say.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Social commentary.
 Anyone can comment about what's happening now and share their thoughts,
 and sometimes those go into conversation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So, that's what we want to make stronger and also easier.
 So, four areas that we've been focused on there.
 Number one is around on-boarding.
 We've been applying a lot more machine learning and deep learning to our
 on-boarding, so we can match people faster to their interests.
 And we believe that that interest drive is really important to us and unique
 to us.
 Two, is the timeline where people spend the majority of their time.
 We've made a number of refinements over the past few months to make sure
 that we're showing what's most important and what really matters, and enabling
 people to quickly get back to everything and to recency.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notifications is another area where we think we can do a much better job,
 especially around breaking news.
 And not that we just push you into a tweet that dead ends, but we can enable
 you to further explore topics around that tweet and that interest.
\end_layout

