\begin_layout Itemize
Pick up a coin C1 given C1+C2 with probability of trials p(h1)=.7, p(h2)=.6
 and doing 10 trials.
 And what is the probability that the given coin you picked is C1 given
 you have 7 heads and 3 tails? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Lets say the population on Facebook clicks ads with a click-through-rate
 of P.
 We select a sample of size N and examine the sample's conversion rate,
 denoted by hat{P}, what is the minimum sample size N such that Probability(
 ABS(hat{P} - P) &lt; DELTA ) = 95%.
 In other words (this is my translation), find the minimum sample size N
 such that our sample estimate hat{P} is within DELTA of the true click
 through rate P, with 95% confidence.
 
\end_layout

