\begin_layout Itemize
Given two tables
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Friend_request (requester_id, sent_to_id, time)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Request_accepted (acceptor_id, requestor_id, time)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Find the overall acceptance rate of requests
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

select 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

	round(100*count(case when b.requestor_id is null then 1 else 0 end)/count(a.reque
ster_id),2) as acceptance_rate 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

from Friend_requests as a 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

left join Request_accepted as b 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

on a.sent_to_id = b.acceptor_id and 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

a.requester_id = b.requestor_id 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

where date(a.time) < date_add(current_date(), "-7", "day")
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
you have a table where you have date, user_id, song_id and count.
 It shows at the end of each day how many times in her history a user has
 listened to a given song.
 So count is cumulative sum.
 You have to update this on a daily basis based on a second table that records
 in real time when a user listens to a given song.
 Basically, at the end of each day, you go to this second table and pull
 a count of each user/song combination and then add this count to the first
 table that has the lifetime count.
 If it is the first time a user has listened to a given song, you won't
 have this pair in the lifetime table, so you have to create the pair there
 and then add the count of the last day.
 Onsite: lots of ads related and machine learning questions.
 How to build an ad model, how to test it, describe a model.
 I didn't do well in some of these.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Outer Join / Union All 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
