\begin_layout Itemize
本行业的工作，相关工作经历详细写， 非本行业的工作，工作经历略写，只往cool了写。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
详细准备简历上的所有。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
HR 面试 详细准备why that company，what's your current role.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Interview
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Always answer questions like you know this industry / business a lot
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Never show that you are gussing, even if you are prepared and smart enough
 to guess it right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Never say you do, you can use....
 always say 
\series bold
we use --- let people believe you are doing the same thing now!
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If you are not sure whether your anwer is correct: 
\series bold
say you never encounter this type of problems below, and then describe how
 you construct
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Think for a while before you answer non-math/stat questions.
 Think the structure of the answer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When answer algorithms / features / models / techniques, 
\series bold
never give short answer!
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Alwasy illustration what this algorithm give you, what's the assumption,
 what's s good or bad for it, or compare it with others
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What the feature mean, positive or negative impact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
also connect it with the real business questions.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
When you not sure: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
describe your reasoning, answer in 1, 2, 3.
 // first, second, all
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the machine learnign problem you gave didn't solve the problem, then
 use business sense / Heuristics / Recursively way
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Example: how if unsupervised clustering didn't just give you two groups
 you want -- good or bad, but give you
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
try to relate to the work you have done
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For too generic questions:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Could you give me context? Or describe the data?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If a question is about a fact, and you are not sure.
 Then answer how you would use the data to reveal the knowlege
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Example: Understanding Ad engagement behavior of high net worth user
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Answer: I'm not sure the exact engagement pattern of those high net-value
 people, But if I see the data, the data can reveal their pattern.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
